FBIS4-34132 "drlat116_j_94001" FBIS-LAT-94-116 Daily Report 16 Jun 1994 Panama Government Suspends Flights to, From Haiti Government Suspends Flights to, From Haiti PA1606004294 Panama City TVN Television Network in Spanish 0000 GMT 16 Jun 94 PA1606004294 Panama City TVN Television Network Spanish BFN [From the "Seven O'Clock National Newscast"] [Excerpt] Acting President Guillermo Ford Boyd chaired the scheduled cabinet meeting at the Presidential Palace. Deputy Foreign Minister Carlos Cordero announced that the government will take steps against Haiti. [Begin recording] [Cordero] In accordance with recommendations made at the recent meeting of foreign ministers in Belen de Para, Brazil, within the context of the OAS General Assembly meeting, Panama issued a decree prohibiting all commercial flights between Panama and Haiti. Acting President Ford signed the decree that also prohibits the issuance of takeoff permits for any flights heading for Haiti. [Unidentified reporter] What criteria were taken into account? [Cordero] The OAS recommendations. This is another diplomatic effort directed at solving the Haitian problem. [end recording] [passage omitted]
